rem ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

rem But wait! If a TXT file exists, and it  IS approved, we should continue as normal.
rem       But if a TXT file exists, and it NOT approved, we should ask before overwriting it.
rem                         It could be a hand-edited txt file that’s years old and has value.
        :if_2180
        iff "%LYRIC_STATUS%" == "" then
                echo %ansi_color_orange%[refresh_lyric_status "%@UNQUOTE[%LYRIC_FILE%]"]%ansi_color_normal%
                gosub  refresh_lyric_status "%@UNQUOTE[%LYRIC_FILE%]"                                           
                echo %ansi_color_orange%[/refresh_lyric_status]%ansi_color_normal%
        endiff
                                                                           
        rem echo %ANSI_COLOR_DEBUG%- DEBUG: TXT_FILE=“%TXT_FILE%”,LYRIC_FILE=“%LYRIC_FILE%”[%@IF[exist "%LYRIC_FILE%",exists,does not exist]],TXT_SIDECAR_FILENAME=“%TXT_SIDECAR_FILENAME%”,LYRIC_STATUS=“%LYRIC_STATUS%”,LYRIClessness_STATUS=“%LYRIClessness_STATUS%”, last_file_to_get_lyric_status_of=“%last_file_to_get_lyric_status_of%”, goto_end="%goto_end%"  %+ pause

        set goto_end=0
        iff not exist "%LYRIC_FILE%"          goto keep_on_truckin_1295
        if "%LYRIC_STATUS%" == "APPROVED"     goto have_acceptable_lyrics_now_or_at_the_very_least_are_done
        if "%LYRIC_STATUS%" == "NOT_APPROVED" goto download_with_lyric_downloader_init
        rem At this point, the lyric_file isn’t approved or not_approved. “NOT_SET” is the technical value.
        rem Since it’s neutral——neither declared unapproved-and-replaceable nor approved-and-irreplaceable——
        rem we must ask for it’s fate. But we should default to “NO” for our answer——because it could be a
        rem previously-hand-edited file from years ago that we care about very much:
                echo %star2% %ansi_color_warning_soft%lyric_file %italics_on%already exists%italics_on% with status: %@IF["APPROVED" == "%lyric_status%",%ansi_color_bright_green%,%ansi_color_bright_red%]%lyric_status%%ansi_color_warning_soft%: %faint_on%“%lyric_file%”%faint_off%%ansi_color_normal%
                :requestion_1347
                unset /q ANSWER hold_answer
                call AskYN "Download %blink_on%new lyrics%blink_off% %underline_on%over%underline_off% existing ones? [%ansi_color_bright_green%A%ansi_color_prompt%pprove them,%ansi_color_bright_green%I%ansi_color_prompt%nstr(%ansi_color_bright_green%X%ansi_color_prompt%=all),%ansi_color_bright_green%L%ansi_color_prompt%yricless,%ansi_color_bright_green%P%ansi_color_prompt%lay,%ansi_color_bright_green%R%ansi_color_prompt%epo-select,%ansi_color_bright_green%F%ansi_color_prompt%]" no %DOWNLOAD_NEW_REPLACEMENT_LYRICS_WAIT_TIME% AILOXPQSF A:Approve_them_instead,I:mark_as_instrumental,X:mark_all_as_instrumentals,L:mark_lyricless,Q:enQueue_in_winamp,P:Preview_it,S:select_from_Repo,O:dOwnload_them_yes_indeedy!,F:fail_whale
                        rem Do instrumental marking if told to:
                                set HOLD_ANSWER_1681=%ANSWER%
                                iff "%HOLD_ANSWER_1681%" == "I" .or. "%HOLD_ANSWER_1681%" == "X" then
                                        gosub check_for_answer_of_I "%@UNQUOTE[%AUDIO_FILE%]"
                                        call AskYN "Abort karaoke creation" yes 120
                                        iff "%ANSWER%" != "N" then
                                                set   abort_karaoke_kreation=1
                                                rem set   goto_end=1
                                                goto /i END_OF_GET_LYRICS
                                        endiff
                                endiff
                        rem Completely abort on “F”:
                                if "%ANSWER%" == "F" .and. "1" == "%QUICK_LRC_MODE%" goto /i :end_quick_lrc_mode_fail
                                if "%ANSWER%" == "F" goto /i :have_acceptable_lyrics_now_or_at_the_very_least_are_done
                        rem Completely abort on “N”:
                                iff "%HOLD_ANSWER_1681%" == "N" then
                                        unset /q ANSWER
                                        call AskYN "Want to try selecting from our repo again" no 30
                                        if   "Y" == "%ANSWER%" goto /i select_from_repo_again
                                        set  abort_karaoke_kreation=1
                                        rem set  goto_end=1
                                        goto /i END_OF_GET_LYRICS
                                endiff
                        rem On “S”, go back to selecting a file from our repo:
                                if "%HOLD_ANSWER_1681%" == "S" goto /i repo_stuffs_begin
                
                        rem On “A”, approve the lyrics, then continue:
                                gosub check_for_answer_of_A
                        rem On “Y”, download new lyrics:
                                iff "%HOLD_ANSWER_1681%" == "Y" .or. "%HOLD_ANSWER_1681%" == "O" then
                                        unset /q lyric_approval
                                        set  goto_end=0
                                        goto download_with_lyric_downloader_init
                                endiff
                        rem On “P”/“Q”, preview:
                                set ANSWER=%HOLD_ANSWER_1681%
                                gosub check_for_answer_of_P "%@UNQUOTE[%AUDIO_FILE%]"
                                gosub check_for_answer_of_Q "%@UNQUOTE[%AUDIO_FILE%]"
                                if  "%HOLD_ANSWER_1681%" == "P" .or. "%HOLD_ANSWER_1681%" == "Q" (goto /i requestion_1347)

                        rem On “L”, mark as lyricless:
                                if "L" == "%HOLD_ANSWER_1681%" (set LYRICS_ACCEPTABLE=0 %+ SET ANSWER=L)
                                gosub check_for_answer_of_L
                        rem If we hit “N” / otherwise decided we’re done, let user know why:
                                echo 🐑🐑🐑 goto_end is “%goto_end%”, LYRIC_STATUS=“%LYRIC_STATUS%”
                                if "1" != "%goto_end%" .or. "APPROVED" == "%LYRIC_STATUS%" goto keep_on_truckin_1295
                                        echo %ansi_color_warning_soft%%star2% Okay then... We’re done, I guess.
                                        echo %ansi_color_warning_soft%%star2% You didn’t %italics_on%approve%italics_off% the above lyrics
                                        echo %ansi_color_warning_soft%%star2% But you %italics_on%also didn’t approve%italics_off% downloading new lyrics to overwrite them
                                        echo %ansi_color_warning_soft%%star2% We are at an impasse.
                                        rem this made doubles when called from get-lyrics-here: gosub divider
                                        goto /i end_OF_GET_LYRICS
                                :keep_on_truckin_1295

                rem echo Hello McFly! if "1" == "%GOTO_END%" .or. "1" == "%ABANDONED_SEARCH%" goto /i END_OF_GET_LYRICS
                if "1" == "%GOTO_END%" .or. "1" == "%ABANDONED_SEARCH%" goto /i END_OF_GET_LYRICS


rem ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
rem Download the lyrics using LYRIC_DOWNLOADER_1: SETUP: —————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————
rem Set the values that we will use when using LYRIC_DOWNLOADER_1 the first time [they get changed during subsequent download attempts]:
        rem Don’t go here unless we haven’t performed our first search yet; otherwise goto download_with_lyric_downloader_1 instead



rem Deal with the fact that we have multiple lyric providers:
        :download_with_lyric_downloader_init
        :download_with_current_provider_init
        

        rem Delete temp files from any previous SyncedLyrics search:
                gosub delete_maybe_files


        :download_with_lyricsgenius_init
                rem DEBUG: call debug ":download_with_lyricsgenius_init: CURRENT_LYRIC_PROVIDER=%CURRENT_LYRIC_PROVIDER% [goat]" silent
                setdos /x0
                *setdos /x-9
                if "1" == "%lyric_downloader_initialized%" goto /i done_with_download_with_lyric_downloader_init
                        set        FILE_SONG_TO_USE=%FILE_SONG%
                        set       FILE_TITLE_TO_USE=%FILE_SONG%          
                        set      FILE_ARTIST_TO_USE=%FILE_ARTIST%
                        set FILE_ORIG_ARTIST_TO_USE=%FILE_ORIG_ARTIST%
                        set       FILE_ALBUM_TO_USE=%FILE_ALBUM%
                        set lyric_downloader_initialized=1
                        rem gosub debug "🎨🎨🎨[40] FILE_ARTIST_TO_USE=“%FILE_ARTIST_TO_USE%, FILE_ARTIST=“%FILE_ARTIST%””"

                :done_with_download_with_lyric_downloader_init
        

rem Download the lyrics using the currently-selected provider: BEGIN: ——————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————

        rem Initialize/debug/audit:
                :download_with_lyric_downloader_1
                rem call debug "current_lyric_provider[BEFRE] = “%current_lyric_provider%”" silent
                gosub refresh_current_lyric_provider_metadatas
                set current_search=%CURRENT_LYRIC_PROVIDER% :::: %FILE_SONG_TO_USE% :::: %FILE_ARTIST_TO_USE%``
                set current_search_song=%FILE_SONG_TO_USE%
                set current_search_artist=%FILE_ARTIST_TO_USE%
                rem call debug "[XX94] Checking %italics_on%current_search%italics_off% of %faint_on%current_search%faint_off% set to %ansi_color_blue%%lq%%current_search%%rq%%ansi_color_normal%, JUST_RENAMED_TO_INSTRUMENTAL=“%JUST_RENAMED_TO_INSTRUMENTAL%”" silent
                rem NO! if "1" == "%QUICK_LRC_MODE%" goto end_quick_lrc_mode_fail

        rem Don’t repeat the same search as the last search:
                iff "%current_search%" == "%last_search%" .and. "%FIRST_SEARCH_COMPLETE%" != "1" then
                        rem Skipping search because
                        echo %ansi_color_warning_soft%%NO% Skipping%blink_off% search because %italics_on%current_search%italics_off% is the same as %italics_on%last_search%italics_off% of “%LAST_SEARCH%”%ansi_color_normal%
                        goto /i skip_only_this_search
                endiff


        rem Don’t repeat previous searches we’ve already made:
                rem OLD: set already_searched_for_this=%[already_searched_for_%file_song_to_use%_%file_artist_to_use%]
                rem NEW:
                set already_searched_for_this=%[already_searched_for_%CURRENT_LYRIC_PROVIDER%_%file_song_to_use%_%file_artist_to_use%]
                set already_searched_for_%CURRENT_LYRIC_PROVIDER%_%[file_song_to_use]_%[file_artist_to_use]=1
                rem DEBUG: echo %ANSI_COLOR_DEBUG%- [DEBUG]  ❶set already_searched_for_%CURRENT_LYRIC_PROVIDER%_%[file_song_to_use]_%[file_artist_to_use]=1
                iff "%already_searched_for_this%" == "1" then
                        rem “skipping earch because we’ve already searched for”
                        echos %ansi_color_bright_red%%NO% %blink_on%Skipping%ansi_color_bright_red% search because we’ve already searched for %ansi_color_warning_soft%“%blink_on%%ansi_color_green%%file_song_to_use%%ansi_color_warning_soft%” 
                        if "" != "%file_artist_to_use%" echos  %blink_on%%ansi_color_bright_red%by %ansi_color_warning_soft%“%ansi_color_green%%blink_on%%file_artist_to_use%%ansi_color_warning_soft%”
                        echos  with %ansi_color_orange%%italics_on%%CURRENT_LYRIC_PROVIDER%%italics_off%
                        echo %blink_off%%ansi_color_normal%
                        goto /i skip_only_this_search
                endiff


        rem At this point, we have to deal with the fact that our supplied Genius.com lyric downloaded DOESN’T HAVE AN OUTPUT FILENAME OPTION
        rem The .JSON file it downloads can be named anything. 
        rem 
        rem So how do we know if a download was successful or not?
        rem 
        rem We must create a temporary file, run the downloader, then see if any files NEWER than our temporary file exist.
        rem
        rem The one caveat is... If any files exist that are dated in the future, it will trip a false negative for our success.
        rem
        rem Thus, we must check for any files that may exist in the future, and re-date them to the current date with the touch utility.
        rem
        rem Our utility check-for-future-dated-files does this:
                if /i "%CURRENT_LYRIC_PROVIDER%" == "LyricsGenius" call check-for-future-dated-files /t


        rem Create a tiny file so we don’t accidentally do anything latest-file based with any pre-existing files in the folder,
        rem Because later we are doing things with the latest file, but if a failure happens, the latest file could be something
        rem already in the folder.  To prevent that, *this* will be the latest file:
                 if /i "%CURRENT_LYRIC_PROVIDER%" == "LyricsGenius" >"__"          


        rem Allow universal override of FILE_ARTIST_TO_USE via environment variable:
                if "" != "%OVERRIDE_FILE_ARTIST_TO_USE%" set FILE_ARTIST_TO_USE=%OVERRIDE_FILE_ARTIST_TO_USE%

        rem Cosmetics:
                iff "1" == "%cover_original_attempt%" then
                        set blink_maybe=%blink_on%
                else                        
                        set blink_maybe=%blink_off%
                endiff
                gosub divider nonewline                                    

        rem Create our command:
                unset /q LYRIC_RETRIEVAL_COMMAND SUBTI_RETRIEVAL_COMMAND EXSUB_RETRIEVAL_COMMAND
                                                                   set LYRIC_RETRIEVAL_COMMAND=%LYRIC_DOWNLOADER_1%%ZZZZ% song "%FILE_SONG_TO_USE%"   "%FILE_ARTIST_TO_USE%" --save
                if /i "%CURRENT_LYRIC_PROVIDER%" == "LyricsGenius" set LYRIC_RETRIEVAL_COMMAND=%LYRIC_DOWNLOADER_1%%ZZZZ% song "%FILE_SONG_TO_USE%"   "%FILE_ARTIST_TO_USE%" --save
                if /i "%CURRENT_LYRIC_PROVIDER%" == "SyncedLyrics" set EXSUB_RETRIEVAL_COMMAND=%LYRIC_DOWNLOADER_2%%ZZZZZZ% "%FILE_SONG_TO_USE%  %FILE_ARTIST_TO_USE%" --enhanced -o "%ELRC_SIDECAR_FILENAME_TEMP%"
                if /i "%CURRENT_LYRIC_PROVIDER%" == "SyncedLyrics" set SUBTI_RETRIEVAL_COMMAND=%LYRIC_DOWNLOADER_2%%ZZZZZZ% "%FILE_SONG_TO_USE%  %FILE_ARTIST_TO_USE%" -o "%LRC_SIDECAR_FILENAME_TEMP%"
                if /i "%CURRENT_LYRIC_PROVIDER%" == "SyncedLyrics" set LYRIC_RETRIEVAL_COMMAND=%LYRIC_DOWNLOADER_2%%ZZZZZZ% "%FILE_SONG_TO_USE%  %FILE_ARTIST_TO_USE%" --plain-only -o "%TXT_SIDECAR_FILENAME_TEMP%"


        rem Quick chance to stop things before we have to sit and wait:
                echo.
                set DISPLAY_NAME=lyric
                if "1" == "%QUICK_LRC_MODE%" set DISPLAY_NAME=quick lrc
                rem “Start lyric search"
                unset /q ARTIST_BLURB
                if "" != "%current_search_artist%" set ARTIST_BLURB= by “%ansi_color_important%%current_search_artist%%ansi_color_less_important%”
                :reask_nextsearch
                call less_important " Next search will be for: “%italics_on%%ansi_color_important%%current_search_song%%italics_off%%ansi_color_less_important%”%ARTIST_BLURB%"
                call askyn          "Start %italics_on%%DISPLAY_NAME%%italics_off% search w/%italics_on%%CURRENT_LYRIC_PROVIDER%%italics_off% [%ansi_color_bright_green%K%ansi_color_prompt%=fail file or folder,e=e%ansi_color_bright_green%D%ansi_color_prompt%it band/artist,mark as %ansi_color_bright_green%I%ansi_color_prompt%nstrumental,%ansi_color_bright_green%P%ansi_color_prompt%lay]" yes 12 KDIP K:fail_file/folder,D:eDit_artist_and_song,I:it_is_an_instrumental_actually,P:play_it_now
                        rem “I”/“D”/“K”:
                                gosub check_for_answer_of_I "%@UNQUOTE[%AUDIO_FILE%]"
                                gosub check_for_answer_of_D
                                gosub check_for_answer_of_K
                        rem “P”:
                                gosub check_for_answer_of_P "%@UNQUOTE[%AUDIO_FILE%]"
                                if "P" == "%ANSWER"% goto /i reask_nextsearch
                        rem Abort/Continue on “K”:
                                call debug "does 1 == %QUICK_LRC_MODE% {quick lrc mode} [answer=%answer%]"
                                if "K" == "%ANSWER%" goto /i :have_acceptable_lyrics_now_or_at_the_very_least_are_done
                        rem “N”:
                                if "N" == "%ANSWER%" goto /i :skip_only_this_search
                        rem Cosmetic:
                                echos %ANSI_MOVE_UP_1%%ANSI_ERASE_TO_EOL%

        rem Print our command:
                echos %BIG_OFF%%@ANSI_CURSOR_COLOR_BY_WORD[yellow]
                echo %BIG_OFF%%ANSI_COLOR_IMPORTANT_LESS%%STAR% %blink_on%Searching%blink_off% for lyrics with %italics_on%%CURRENT_LYRIC_PROVIDER%%italics_off% for %ansi_color_important%“%ansi_color_pink%%italics_on%%FILE_SONG_TO_USE%%italics_off%%ansi_color_important%”%ansi_color_important_less%%@IF["" != "%FILE_ARTIST_TO_USE%", by ,]%ansi_color_pink%%italics_off%%blink_maybe%%FILE_ARTIST_TO_USE%%blink_off%%ansi_color_important_less%...%italics_off%%ANSI_RESET%%conceal_on%[1119]%conceal_off%

        rem Store our command in history:
                set last_search=%CURRENT_LYRIC_PROVIDER% :::: %FILE_SONG_TO_USE% :::: %FILE_ARTIST_TO_USE%``


        rem Store that we’ve already searched for this particular:
                rem OLD:                set      already_searched_for_%[file_song_to_use]_%[file_artist_to_use]=1     %+ rem Attach the fact that we’ve performed a Genius search for this file temporarily to the current environemnt session                
                rem NEW:
                set already_searched_for_%CURRENT_LYRIC_PROVIDER%_%[file_song_to_use]_%[file_artist_to_use]=1
                rem DEBUG: echo %ANSI_COLOR_DEBUG%- [DEBUG] %italics_on%   last_search%italics_off% set to %ansi_color_orange%"%last_search%"%ansi_color_normal% 666GOAT
                rem DEBUG: echo %ANSI_COLOR_DEBUG%- [DEBUG]  ❷set already_searched_for_%CURRENT_LYRIC_PROVIDER%_%[file_song_to_use]_%[file_artist_to_use]=1      666GOAT
                rem DEBUG: echo %ANSI_COLOR_DEBUG%- [DEBUG]  LYRIC_RETRIEVAL_COMMAND=%LYRIC_RETRIEVAL_COMMAND%      666GOAT


        rem moved below: rem Tag the file as having been searched this way already ONLY AFTER we’ve done it, because this can update the date which holistically thwarts the download process:
        rem moved below:         set provider_type_for_adb_tag=genius
        rem moved below:         if /i "%CURRENT_LYRIC_PROVIDER%" == "SyncedLyrics" set provider_type_for_adb_tag=syncedlyrics
        rem moved below:         if /i "%CURRENT_LYRIC_PROVIDER%" == "LyricsGenius" set provider_type_for_adb_tag=genius
        rem moved below:         echo True>"%@UNQUOTE["%audio_file%"]:%provider_type_for_adb_tag%_searched_already"                 %+ rem Attach the fact that we’ve performed a Genius search for this file permanently to the file itself using ADS tag

        rem Unicode/Emoji voodoo: Store original environment variable value for PYTHONIOENCODING:            
                if defined PYTHONIOENCODING (set PYTHONIOENCODING_OLD=%PYTHONIOENCODING%)
                set PYTHONIOENCODING=utf-8

        rem Run our command, with a “y” answer to overwrite:
